message.content:
cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.CC, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with first-order logic and its complexity.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as intuitionistic logic is used in some areas of AI, such as automated reasoning and natural language processing.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possibility as the paper discusses fragments of logic that can be used in programming language semantics.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper studies the complexity of different fragments of intuitionistic logic.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the decidability and complexity of fragments of logic, which can be seen as a type of algorithmic problem.
